{
  "texts": [
    "Many narratives in this dataset were transcribed (1) without much punctuation and (2) without removing uninformative speech (e.g., 'I don't know, we went to, I guess, well,').",
    "These two factors do not affect manual scoring, but could significantly impact automated scoring.",
    "Narratives with little punctuation are problematic for our approach because it leads pySBD to split narratives into sentences incorrectly.",
    "Resulting segments of text contained multiple sentences, which makes accurate prediction difficult for the model.",
    "While our preprocessing removed very long pieces of text without punctuation, some pieces of text still contained multiple sentences."
  ]
}